<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>PLAN — {{PROJECT_NAME}}</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="experiments/research.css">
</head>
<!-- HUMAN-FACING PLAN — the styled twin of PLAN.md. PLAN.md stays the canonical,
     Claude-facing file (agents read and edit it; experiment cards reference
     `PLAN.md §<phase>`; validate_structure requires it). This HTML is what a human
     opens in a browser; keep the two in sync the same way README.md/README.html
     are kept in sync — when you change one, mirror the change in the other.
     Lives at the project root and links the shared design system that onboarding
     copies into experiments/ (no extra copy at root). If experiments/ is renamed
     or absent, point these two links at any copy of research.css/research.js.
     Keep, drop, or repeat sections as the plan needs — the TOC builds itself from
     the <h2>/<h3> headings. -->
<body>
<div class="page-wrap">

  <nav class="sidebar" aria-label="Table of contents">
    <div class="sidebar-brand">
      <div class="sidebar-brand-name">{{PROJECT_SHORT_NAME}}
        <span>Plan</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="sidebar-title">Contents</p>
    <div id="toc-list"></div>
  </nav>

  <div class="main-content">
    <header class="spec-header">
      <h1>PLAN — {{PROJECT_NAME}}</h1>
      <table class="meta-table">
        <tbody>
          <tr><th>Kind</th>    <td>Research plan</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Canonical</th><td><code>PLAN.md</code> (this is its human-facing twin)</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Owner</th>   <td>{{PLAN_OWNER}}</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Date</th>    <td>{{DATE}}</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <div class="claude-note">
        <code>PLAN.md</code> governs the project: objectives, phases, gates, and the
        experiment matrix. Cards reference this plan; a card that doesn't fit the plan
        is a plan-change proposal, not a card. Plan changes are human decisions
        (<code>reference/human-in-the-loop-policy.md</code>).
      </div>
    </header>

    <main>

      <section id="objectives">
        <h2>1. Objectives</h2>
        <p>Numbered, owner-confirmed goals.</p>
        <ol>
          <li>{{OBJECTIVE_1}}</li>
          <li>{{OBJECTIVE_2}}</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section id="current-state">
        <h2>2. Current state / prior work</h2>
        <p>What exists now: prior publications, baselines, reference code, checkpoints.</p>
        <p>{{PRIOR_WORK}}</p>
      </section>

      <section id="phases">
        <h2>3. Phases &amp; gates</h2>
        <p>Each phase has a <strong>quantitative gate</strong> and a named approver. A
          gate is declared passed only by the approver, on a confirmed verdict (never
          by Claude).</p>

        <h3>Phase 1 — {{PHASE_1_NAME}}</h3>
        <div class="req-row"><span class="req-id">Work</span><span>{{PHASE_1_WORK}}</span></div>
        <div class="req-row"><span class="req-id">Gate</span><span>{{PHASE_1_GATE_CRITERION}} — approver: {{PHASE_1_APPROVER}}</span></div>

        <h3>Phase 2 — {{PHASE_2_NAME}}</h3>
        <div class="req-row"><span class="req-id">Work</span><span>{{PHASE_2_WORK}}</span></div>
        <div class="req-row"><span class="req-id">Gate</span><span>{{PHASE_2_GATE_CRITERION}} — approver: {{PHASE_2_APPROVER}}</span></div>

        <!-- If the project's evaluation metric or pass criterion is not yet defined,
             leave it as an explicit TODO gate here; the reviewer blocks dependent
             experiments until it is defined. -->
      </section>

      <section id="matrix">
        <h2>4. Experiment matrix</h2>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>ID</th><th>What varies</th><th>Phase</th><th>Status</th><th>Gate result</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>{{E_ID}}</td><td>{{WHAT_VARIES}}</td><td>{{PHASE}}</td><td>{{STATUS}}</td><td>{{GATE_RESULT}}</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>Kept consistent with <code>experiments/registry.json</code> (source of truth).</p>
      </section>

      <section id="risks">
        <h2>5. Risks &amp; mitigations</h2>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Risk</th><th>Mitigation</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>{{RISK}}</td><td>{{MITIGATION}}</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section id="decisions">
        <h2>6. Decisions taken</h2>
        <p>Pointer to the decision log: <code>decisions/</code>. Significant
          methodological choices and rejected options are recorded there, not here.</p>
      </section>

    </main>
  </div>
</div>
<script src="experiments/research.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
